President Muhammadu Buhari of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Alhaji Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples’ Democratic Party (PDP) and Omoyele Sowore of the African Action Congress (ACC) topped the list of presidential aspirant who performed well at a poll conducted by CitizenPoll.
Buhari led other contestants polling 64.52 per cent of the votes with a total of 8348 votes, while Atiku of the PDP came second with 3,241 votes, representing 25 per cent of the vote.
The Poll which featured only eight Presidential Candidates, has Mrs Oby Ezekwesili of Allied Congress Party of Nigeria (ACPN) trailing at the bottom with only 163 votes being 1.11 per cent of the poll as at the time of this report.
In the 3rd position on the poll was Omoyele Sowore of African Action Congress (ACC) who polled 344 (2.66%), followed by Kingsley Moghalu of Young Progressive Party (YPP) with 264 votes (2.04%).
Tope Dasua of the Abundant Nigeria Renewal Party (ANRP) polled 215 votes (1.66%) while in the 6th position as at the time of this report was Donald Duke of the Social Democratic Party (SDP) with 195 votes (1.51%).
Another picture from the poll shows Ezekwesili trailing with the least amount of votes
The seventh position was occupied by Fela Durotoye with 190 votes representing 1.47 per cent of the votes.
The Citizen Poll also had another running online poll of worst performing Governor in Nigeria with Gov. Yahaya Bello of Kogi topping the 10-man list.
 
